- In this context, "treasure chests of successful deliveries" refers to categories and sub-categories of products with delivered orders; 
- "gold coins representing the total sales" means the total amount of sales for each category and sub-category; 
- "a bounty worth more than a single coin" refers to the condition that the total sales must be greater than zero.

- 'lowest average product ratings' refers to the minimum average rating within each main category;
- 'main categories' are categories that contain sub-categories;
- 'sub-categories' are categories that contain products;
- 'average product ratings' are calculated based on the product ratings given by users (e.g., 1-5).
